Author: Ale88
Title: [ANN] UBIATAR-AIRDROP -ICO-CRYPTOCURRENCY TO BE EVERYWHERE
Body: As some of you may already know, I’ve been the first one to raise some doubts regarding UbiatarPlay’s behavior, especially in the Italian forum, we’re talking about mid/end May, related to the bounty and the airdrop since a few days after I asked explanations to Francesco Raco, one of the foundrs, he blocked me on Telegram without any reason, he also attacked me on a public Italian chat saying that I insulted him and that I was a liar but, unfortunately for him, I had already sent the private conversation to the admins, so he decided to disappear, weird, eh?  During the last months things got worse and worse, UbiatarPlay people just kept lying and lying regarding everything, showing no respect for the investors or the bounty hunters , bounty hunters that have worked for 3 months, I repeat, 3 MONTHS, to get a few dollars, because they distributed a 5-10% of what they promised.  Here’s a quick recap of what happened: - As I said they paid only 5-10% of what they promised; - They said the old spreadsheet was wrong so it took them months to make a new one, or at lest this is what they say, and they can’t publish it because the European Union doesn’t allow them to publish the ETH wallets’ public addresses; - In order to pay less tokens, they started saying that there were more than 20k bounty hunters in the new spreadsheet while in the old one there were less than 2k, also remember that in their Telegram chat there are only 11k people, how is it possible to have more bounty hunters than users, especially considering that to get the bounty you must join the Telegram chat? - The number of users in the Telegram chat is fake, they bought hundreds, or thousands, of profiles, you just have to check the users list and it’s easy to spot them; - Heavy censorship in the Telegram chat, deleted posts and users banned without any warning after they asked stuff they didn’t like; - They manage all the bounty and airdrop problems by e-mail, in this way they think they can hide the truth from the users without posting in public; - Fake reviews in the online stores to increase the rating of their app, one of the reviewers even has an Ubiatar logo as profile picture… - Telegram chat with no real interest from the users, so they thought to change their own profiles and make them look like new users, very enthusiastic about the app, so they ask questions and also answer them, they’re such a losers…   Especially regarding the last point I decided to waste some time to show you how they think to be smart, considering the whole community as poor idiots, I attach you some screenshots:  Here we have 3 posts and we can read 4 different name: Chantal writes, Nina says hello calling her Giulia and Chantal replies calling her Martha!    Jennifer says hello and Chantal calls her Tony, because, in the meantime she changed sex      John Frings says hello and they reply with "Hello Anna", again, another one who changed sex…   And then John Frings/Anna becomes AnnaKate... And below you can notice a quoted post from Mirko, and they call him Peter    And now Martha, I love Martha, she’s great! Here she’s answering to Giulia, her colleague, calling her Dory:   Here she plays dumb asking how to be an avatar, and of course Chantal answers calling her Matthew, so once again, new sex…   And I think it’s a bit weird that Martha doesn’t know how to be an avatar, here she answers as Admin…   Now Martha became Danish, after changing sex she decided to change nationality as well:   And it’s weird, here she says she’s Italian,who knows, maybe the hormones confused her…    Who was Danish? From Vejle? Oh yeah, Martha! But wait, now she’s Mirko, she’s a male again?!    Another change of profile, Nina gets called as Moka    In Switzerland must be easy to find a job, one day you don’t even know what you’re talking about…   …and he next day you’re a mode, unbelievable! Congratulations Tony!    Yet another new name, Vladislav becomes Nadine, you know…    And if you still have some doubts, here’s some screenshot from a private conversation with a mod that changed name several times…      This is what they’re doing to make people (and investors) believing that there actually are people interested in this project, when in the reality nobody cares anymore about them, just to give you another number the Telegram chat loses 200 users per week.  As soon as they get quoted (if they get quoted) this token from 2 dollars will dump directly to a few cents.   So remember, these people are SCAMMERS!

Author: safariwave
Title: [ANN] UBIATAR-AIRDROP -ICO-CRYPTOCURRENCY TO BE EVERYWHERE
Body: Airdrop fulfillment  Now that the ICO has ended, it is time for us to proceed with all airdrops.  In an older email we requested some documents from all subscribers in order to be compliant with the Swiss legislation as it evolved in the last few weeks.  This has been superseded by a subsequent update, so your documents are no longer needed; any data anybody sent to us in the meantime has been deleted from our archives.   Please kindly answer to this email with the following informations: - your Eidoo wallet address  We will cross reference the address with data provided by eidoo to check for compliance with the airdrop rules. As soon as we validate all your informations  we will proceed with the transfer of the correct amount of UAC to the address you specified. If you need more informations about our airdrop process, you can see our airdrop explanation page or learn about the ubiatarplay project  and see for yourself.  UbiatarPlay SA will use the data you provide only for the purpose of the fulfillment of the procedure describe into this message. Your informations will be kept in a safe storage and shared only with other organizations needed for the completion of the requested procedures. For more informations see our privacy-policy: http://ubiatarplay.io/ubiatar-privacy-policy

Author: yeswepump
Title: [ANN] UBIATAR-AIRDROP -ICO-CRYPTOCURRENCY TO BE EVERYWHERE
Body: it is written in italian by Francesco:  UbiatarPlay . Mercoledi 22 Maggio 2018  Abbiamo ricevuto molte critiche riguardo l’iniziativa PowerFriendship, alcune piuttosto pesanti.  Vogliamo ribadire come questa ed altre iniziative siano state prese nell’interesse esclusivo del progetto e dei molti sottoscrittori.  La raccolta della ICO è importante ai fini della promozione di una piattaforma che sarà un marketplace e quindi dipenderà esclusivamente dal recepimento del pubblico.  Quando si offre all’umanità un nuovo potere, occorre far recepire tale possibilità ad un mondo che prima non ne aveva consaoevolezza.  Questo richiede un grosso sforzo di comunicazione.  Le risorse raccolte finora sono sufficienti per queso scopo, ma l’obiettivo prefissato per una rapidissima crescita iniziale non sarà probabilmente raggiunto a causa di procedure troppo complesse per il soddisfacimento di norme di registrazione dei partecipanti imposte dalla legislazione degli ultimi mesi.  Al solo scopo di velocizzare le operazioni e offrire un premio a chi aiutasse suoi amici in questo complicatissimo, ma necessario, processo abbiamo proposto un premio consistente a chi prendesse impegni concreti.  Assistiamo ora ad una levata di scudi da parte di chi ha già sottoscritto la ICO. Costoro credono che il loto impegno venga sminuito e ci si ritrovi con troppi ubiatarcoin in circolazione.  Il numero totale di UAC della ICO è fisso e non verrebbe variato da questa iniziativa.  Il prezzo di vendita è stato molto vantaggioso per tutti e un ulteriore sconto per spingere nuovi sottoscrittori non ne cambierebbe la valutazione minima che ci siamo sempre impegnati a mantenere a due dollari nel marketplace UbiatarPlay.  Tuttavia, il successo del progetto dipende dalla collaborazione e la promozione di tutti è anche piú importante della raccolta fondi.  Se i sottoscrittori non comprendono lo scopo e la portata reale di una iniziativa, riteniamo di doverli ascoltare.  Tutto questo considerato, ho deciso di sospendere l’iniziativa, garantendo comunque ai pochi che hanno già portato a termine le segnalazioni il risultato promesso. Si tratta di pochissime persone per importi modesti.  Ringraziamo comunque tutti i sottoscrittori e assicuriamo che il progetto procederà come descritto puntualmente nel White Paper online, con i fondi che già ora sono sufficienti per la pubblicazione e promozione della piattaforma.  Grazie a tutti

Body: This are the steps I'm seeing in the Telegram group...    🚁 Airdrop 🚁 For the airdrop follow these steps:  1. To receive the initial 10 UAC download the Eidoo app on your mobile device and register. Your wallet Eidoo wallet needs to be active and with at least 0.01 ETH before the 9th of May at 9 a.m CET.  2. For 20 UAC first complete step 1 and then register on icoengine.net , then confirm registration. Complete the their 1 in the identification tab  3. For 130 UAC follow step 1 &2 and then complete Tier 2 of KYC (know your customer) in the Identification tab on icoengine.net  4. To receive the Uac 10, 20 or 130  you will also need to download the UbiatarPlay app and set yourself as available on the app. Furthermore you need to join our Telegram channel Ubiatarplay Official, then write a message with this text   «I am on ubiatar as (username). Instead of (username) you have to write the username you used in Ubiatar App registration.  You'll receive your free tokens 15 days after the ending of the ICO on your Eidoo wallet.                                   — For more information about the Airdrop take a look at our website: http://ubiatarplay.io/eidoo-ubiatar-airdrop/

You'll receive your free tokens 15 days after the ending of the ICO on your Eidoo wallet.                                   For more information about the Airdrop take a look at our website: http://ubiatarplay.io/eidoo-ubiatar-airdrop/

Author: wolfgb888
Title: [ANN] UBIATAR-AIRDROP -ICO-CRYPTOCURRENCY TO BE EVERYWHERE
Body: UbiatarPlay will be the peer-to-peer marketplace of the ubiatar service. Ubiatar   delivers   the   power of ubiquity with modern mobile technologies, over a high-performance platform. The starting point is a normal smartphone held by a local individual (the  Avatar); everything that is seen and heard by the Avatar is sent over the network to the Person at home (Usar) that in turn directs the Avatar so that he/she acts as his/her remote body.  The directions are given with a revolutionary GUI (Graphical User Interface) superimposed over the live video stream. Avatars and Usars will meet on the UbiatarPlay marketplace, just like publishers ofer apps on the Apple Store and Google Play to customers all over the world.

Title: [ANN] UBIATAR-AIRDROP -ICO-CRYPTOCURRENCY TO BE EVERYWHERE
Body: To access Ubiatar's airdop you need the Eidoo wallet and you must be validated up to tier2 at www.icoengine.net The Eidoo wallet is mandatory to participate in the Ubiatar ICO too, as the ICO Engine is also used in this case. To purchase UAC tokens up to 3,000 USD (minimum investment 0.1 ETH) tier1 is sufficient; for purchases of higher amounts tier2 is required.  The Eidoo wallet is installed by more than 100,000 devices and the people who made the KYC at Eidoo are almost 15,000. For the new ICOs using the Eidoo's services at this point becomes increasingly convenient as they start from a very large base of potential customers and reachable with a simple alert in the Eidoo wallet.  This mandatory KYC thing is becoming more pervasive, I don't know until it can be avoided.

I have given my personal details to a lot of fantom airdrops and got anything. This is a serious project and Eidoo/Ubiatar are rewarding users that want to partecipate to this and other ico... that's why the ask to register and do KYC to icoengine!

Author: davide72
Title: [ANN] UBIATAR-AIRDROP -ICO-CRYPTOCURRENCY TO BE EVERYWHERE
Body: I completely agree with your position, KYC is not scam, we are free to do it or not is up to us . Major exchange you have to do it if you like to trade and withdrawal anyway.

Author: yeswepump
Title: [ANN] UBIATAR-AIRDROP -ICO-CRYPTOCURRENCY TO BE EVERYWHERE
Body: At first, I also didn't like the KYC request, but reading the general state trend to "regulate" ico world, I think this is a due step, in order to avoid/limit ico scam. Of course we loose our "crypto privacy" but at the end it's our decision: we can stay out of the ico world, if we don't like the KYC.
